config GOOGLE_DA9188_REGULATOR
	tristate "Google DA9188 Regulator driver"
	depends on GOOGLE_MFD_DA9188
	help
	  Enable support for the DA9188 AP-PMIC regulator driver.
	  This driver provide the regulator instance for the other device driver
	  to use as their power supplies. The regulator binding is specified in
	  the DTS.
	  Select Y if you have such device.

config GOOGLE_DA9188_REGULATOR_REGISTER_ACCESS
	bool "Debugfs PMIC register access support"
	depends on GOOGLE_DA9188_REGULATOR
	depends on DEBUG_FS
	help
	  Enable direct PMIC register access support via debugfs.
	  It provides a debugfs directory to read / write PMIC
	  registers, under /sys/kernel/debug/pmic/.
	  Select Y if you need to use it for debugging.
	  If unsure select "N".

